collections.name: Geometric Echoes II
collections.description:
"Geometric Echoes" is a collection of unique digital artworks exploring the interplay of geometry, spirituality, and the natural world. Drawing inspiration from ancient cultures and the profound beauty of nature, I have meticulously crafted each piece using Adobe Illustrator, employing a range of digital effects to manipulate basic geometric shapes into intricate patterns and textures.

This collection is a testament to the power of human creativity and the endless possibilities of digital art. Each artwork is a one-of-a-kind expression of my artistic vision, inviting viewers to contemplate the underlying order and harmony found within the universe.
These are my own, hand-crafted geometric abstraction artworks. To enhance the visual experience, I employed AI animation techniques, but the core artwork remains my original, human-created design.

collections.name: Age of Empires
collections.description:
Age of Empires - A Tribute to the Great Civilizations Through Digital Masks
Age of Empires is a unique NFT collection of 444 digital masks inspired by the 5 greatest empires in human history:
 Japan
 China
 Greece
 Italy (Venice)
 Aztec Empire
Each mask is more than just a digital work of art. It is a cultural artifact created with respect for the history, mythology and aesthetics of each era. The project seeks to preserve cultural heritage through Web3, making it available in a new format - digital, collectible and timeless.

collections.name: Extended Garden - Fifth State
collections.description:
‘Once Upon A Garden’ is a digitally composited garden presenting a dystopian projection of a likely outcome of global warming. It depicts a world where humans now have to live with simulated images of plants and flowers because they have all disappeared from earth. It asks whether the preservation of nature is compatible with the goals of industrialised and industrialising societies, and in general is a reflection on what gets left behind in our pursuit of progress.

‘Once Upon a Garden’ is ultimately a GAN (generative adversarial network) trained on thousands of images of extinct and endangered flora from the Sahel region, where I was born and live. It was created with the intent to be an installation that mimics walking through an artificial garden, and all the sorrow and beauty that this implies.

The extended gardens build on previous gardens in this body of work, and add more species under new light conditions. They are longer, more immersive garden experiences that invite deeper meditation on flora we lost.

collections.name: Faces
collections.description: Faces" is a mesmerising art piece that captures the essence of human expression through a vibrant, abstract lens. This digital artwork features a striking silhouette of overlapping profiles, each layer infused with a chaotic yet harmonious blend of colors—electric blues, fiery pinks, and deep blacks—splashed across a textured canvas. The piece evokes a sense of duality and introspection, as the faces seem to merge and diverge, reflecting the complexity of identity and emotion. Created by artist Gerhard Vd Westhuizen, "Faces" combines street art influences with digital innovation. The jagged edges and dripping hues add a raw, visceral energy, while the subtle details invite viewers to explore deeper meanings. Perfect for collectors seeking bold, thought-provoking art, with visual storytelling in the digital age that challenges perception and sparks conversations.

collections.name: Birds of a Feather
collections.description:
“Birds of a Feather” takes flight across 150 unique one-of-one works, each blending or bouncing between the distinctive styles of past Orangehare artists—from the vibrant pop of Yuki to the austere quiet of JJ Roads. Created as an Orangehare In-House Production, the collection reimagines familiar aesthetics through a shared motif: birds. Whether perched alone or flocking in formation, each piece nests in its own ra
rity tier, from “Solo Flyers” to the elusive “Full Flock.” With styles merging, remixing, and migrating across each work, Birds of a Feather is a celebration of the Orangehare roost—proof that when artists take flight together, birds of a feather don’t just flock together… they belong together

collections.name: The Banana
collections.description: Here we have the peak of modern art: a banana, heroically clinging to a wall by the sheer willpower of a single piece of duct tape. It's bold. It's yellow. It's slightly bruised. Some call it a commentary on capitalism, others call it lunch. Either way, this fruity masterpiece proves once and for all that with enough confidence (and tape), anything can be art.

collections.name: Civilization Beyond the Singularity: The Game Begins
collections.description:
Game Civilization is a post-singularity vision of humanity where labor is obsolete, and life is redefined through the philosophy of Play. This collection anchors the cultural core of that vision — a world where purpose comes not from work, but from voluntary engagement, status through mastery, and creativity as survival.


It features the official manifesto, anthem, and symbol of the civilization. Rooted in fairness, UBI, and the cult of meaningful Games, this is not a fantasy — it’s a possible future. "In Game we grow, in Game we elevate."

collections.name: Mochi The Rabbit
collections.description: This artwork is based on original photos of my pet rabbit, Mochi. It was rendered using ChatGPT to create a soft, animated look inspired by storybook-style visuals. The result is an AI-assisted reimagination built from real-life images.
